<section id="budget">
  <div class="page">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">Don't Want to Build?</span>
    <h2 class="big-title reveal">Cheapest Beds <em>Worth Buying</em></h2>
    <p class="intro reveal">Pre-made beds range from genuinely excellent to a waste of money. These categories represent real value at each price point. Each card links to a live Google search so you're always seeing current pricing — not numbers that went stale six months ago.</p>
    <div class="budget-grid">

      <div class="budget-card reveal">
        <span class="budget-badge badge-diy">Free / Near-Free</span>
        <div class="budget-price"><sup>from </sup>$0</div>
        <h4>Stacked Cinder Blocks</h4>
        <p>No kit needed. Buy concrete blocks from any hardware store and stack them in a rectangle — one course for a 7-inch bed, two courses for 15 inches. Drill or cut holes in the caps to plant herbs in the walls themselves. No tools, no screws, instant setup.</p>
        <div class="budget-specs"><span class="spec-chip">Any size</span><span class="spec-chip">7–15 in depth</span><span class="spec-chip">Permanent</span></div>
        <ul class="budget-pros"><li>Zero tools needed</li><li>Blocks can be repurposed</li><li>Herb pockets in wall cavities</li></ul>
        <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=cinder+block+raised+garden+bed+cheap" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="search-btn">🔍 Search Prices Near You</a>
      </div>

      <div class="budget-card reveal">
        <span class="budget-badge badge-diy">Free if sourced</span>
        <div class="budget-price"><sup>from </sup>$0</div>
